			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What is wrong with these young bards today?<a name="4494"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 03 11:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I just wanted to relate some of my recent experiences you the members of this forum.  I would like mention that I am playing on the Brell Serilis server and that my main is a 45th Bard.  I realize that doesn't make me an expert on bards but please bare with me anyway.
<br />

<br />
I created a Druid alt a few months ago to play with some friends of mine that recently joined EQ.  Every time a bard asked for a group I enthusiastically invited them, knowing how much they could help.  Here is a recounting of my experiences so far:
<br />

<br />
1)  The first bard to join our group was in High Hold Pass at the orc camp.  I noticed early on that, while he was a decent mezzer, he refused to twist songs.  I asked him if he knew how to twist and he said yes.  I asked him why he wasn't twisting and got no reply.  The entire time he was in our group he would have either Hymn, Anthem or the Mez song going.  Never two at once.
<br />

<br />
2)  The second bard to join us must have thought he was a tank.  Only two songs came out of him the entire time he was in the group.  He played Anthem while fighting and Hymn while waiting.  He was always in the middle of the fighting and never once mezzed.  Once again I attempted to educate him on the finer points of a Bard's capabilities but go nowhere.
<br />

<br />
3)  Last, but certainly not least, the other night a 22nd Level Bard joined our Unrest basement group.  She was the opposite of Bard number 2.  She refused to fight!  She sat back with the 2 clerics in the group and played mana song exclusively.  When asked why she refused to fight she said, and I quote: &quot;I don't want to die.&quot;  Yes, she was a bit low level to be fighting in the basement but there were 2 clerics and 2 paladins in there to keep her alive.
<br />

<br />
Sorry for the rant but nothing in this game drives me crazier than seeing someone play their bard so badly and refuse to take advise.  The last one really made me shake my head.  I keep trying to convince my friends that Bards are great for groups but I can tell that with each succesive Bard Flop they believe me less and less.
<br />

<br />
Anyone else seeing these things or have I just been really unlucky recently?
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Saetar Silvertongue - Song Weaver of the 51st Season
