			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What is wrong with these young bards today?<a name="4497"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 19 03 12:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes I have noticed this as well, and I think that I know at least one of the reasons.  With PoP, people are actually starting to understand how powerful bards can be when used correctly, particularly in the aspects of swarm and chant kiting.  They look at bards doing these things and say, hey that is awesome I wanna do that, so they go and make a bard.  Unfortunately, the main problem with this logic is twofold, one, we all know you can't really swarm or chant kite effectively until higher levels, and two, they are completely blind to the amount of work necessary to play a bard correctly.  Hence you get people like the ones you met, they don't know their class and they refuse to take advice.  People like that typically don't make it past level 20 or 30 as a bard though.  Anyway, that is my take on why some of this is happening.  Now granted, not all people who make a twink bard are like that, but I have met enough people who are that I am convinced this is one of the problems.  Best thing we can do is to keep trying to educate them as we see them, its all we can do.
<br />

<br />
Aamandor Taleweaver
<br />
62 Virtuoso
<br />
Hand of Valor
<br />
Innoruuk Server</span></td>
