				<td colspan="2"><span>OK, Gotta put my 2cp in here since I'm a twinked newbie bard and you're all bashing me along with those others by grouping us in generalities. I spend at LEAST an hour a day here looking at info to better myself. I have printouts of ALL the info for songs, have made a seperate file &amp; printout that covers only the places to purchase each song. I purchase the next 5 songs that I will need before I reach those levels, I twist my A** off (which considering it's size doesn't really hurt that much). I've worked on my Baking alot, tailoring and Jewelry making a little, mainly stopped those because I was told it was a waste of my time. I've gone from level 1-25 in 4 weeks mostly soloing. I was PL'd for my first 3 levels, mainly someone healing me so I didn't die immediately, (this was before twinking). 
<br />
I meet people all the time who are nice and helpful, they give me tips, PP, and general help. I have what must be the world's biggest lag issue, but I've learned to live with it. If I group I warn people that if I die, it could be 10-15 minutes before I'm back with them, depending on if I have to zone alot. I've disbanded myself more than once so that the group could invite someone else rather than wait for me. Most of them wait for me anyway. I've made friends with numerous High level characters, from more guilds than I can name. I can't even group with these people, but they'll chat with me and sometimes go out of their way to come help me with buffs or equipment that they think is better than mine.
<br />
I also meet A**holes regularly. Yesterday, in Marus Seru (sp?) I grouped with both a cleric and druid who did NOTHING!! They sat at the top of a hill let me tank, and twist, no buffs, no help from them AT ALL! Then they complained when I told them I was leaving the group. Soloing today I died 3 times, but at least I knew it was my fault and not because my group wasn't doing their part.
<br />
People, It's not just bards who need educating. Some of us NEW bards work our butts off learning the ins and outs of what we can do with each new song, (BTW that cataloging song sucks, haven't found a good place to use it yet.) I try to keep all of my music skills maxed, only my slashing skill is any good for fighting....
<br />

