What I DO see, though, are a lot of twinked alts trying to act 'uber' and get the 'phat lewts' yada yada yada and not do much else to help their groups or themselves. Do all the twinks or new bards do this? Course not. But a lot of them do without a clue and it's a tad frustrating sometimes.
<br />

<br />
Case in point: Few months back I was in oot killing Allizesaur and heard in /ooc &quot;Need some help with Quag.&quot; T'was a level 42 bard wanting his epic piece. I immediately responded and went to help the lad. Minute or so later Quag is no more and he has his piece. Not only did the bard not know how to kite he also didn't have 2/3 of the songs of his level. 
<br />

<br />
I asked him how he got to his level without using our assortment of songs and his answer ...well...he said he , &quot;hadn't 'needed' them yet.&quot; 
<br />

<br />
Case in point as he rises in levels and sends me 'links' of the loot he's aquiring and he seems to be learning as he goes. It's a long road for everyone...just some harder than others. 
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />
Trubadour Goldensong
<br />
61st singer
<br />
Tunare</span></td>
