				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What is wrong with these young bards today?<a name="4588"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 21 03 11:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As your first character, bards are one of the more difficult classes to learn to play well, so I wouldn't be too upset that you didn't learn to twist before 30.  You had a more difficult time getting to 30 than if you were twisting, but you did it.
<br />

<br />
As for twisting like there's no tomorrow, yeah its work, hard work at times.  But that's what bards do, that's what is expected of bards, and we can so why not?
<br />

<br />
That being said, I get downtime, I play manasong in downtimes, and if I go AFK in battle I chose one song to play and just head to grab a drink of water (letting group / raid leader know I'll be right back).  
<br />

<br />
When I want to take a break, I move to trader mode and go read a book, or if I want to still play EQ, I switch to my alts.  Sometimes I rest my fingers etc. by, heaven forbid, using the mouse to twist.
<br />

<br />
Our power is in our ability to twist songs on the run.  No other class can do it.  Take that ability away from a bard and he's a lousy tank, pure and simple.  We have litterally half the hps of a pure tank and hit for about half to 2/3 damage over time as they do.
<br />

<br />
I'm sure if you and your group agree, you can work something out, but rest assured that if your group has the choice of a twisting and a non-twisting bard, the twister will win out. IMHO, no one song is as powerful as 3 songs 5 levels below it.  So I'd rather have a level 55 bard twist 3 or 4 songs, than a level 60 twisting one (even Rondo).
<br />

<br />
I don't love it, but I love what it does for myself and my group.  Let's just say if they took away twisting, I am not sure I'd play my bard anymore.  If that means I love it than fine, but my mind is always racing on ways to cheat and have the computer twist for me, hehe.
<br />

<br />
I'll end with my guild's name... To each his own!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
